\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 (3 to 4-pound) boneless {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chuck/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chuck}} roast\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon House Seasoning, recipe follows\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons vegetable oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup thinly sliced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/onion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 onion}} wedges\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cloves garlic, crushed\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 bay leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 (10 3/4-ounce) can {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cream}} of mushroom {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/soup/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 soup}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup red wine\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/worcestershire-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Worcestershire sauce}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon beef {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/bouillon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 bouillon}} granules\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup water\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.\
\
Add the House Seasoning, salt and pepper to a small bowl. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rub/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Rub}} seasoning into the roast on both sides. Heat oil in a large skillet and brown the roast, searing it on both sides. Place the meat in a roaster pan. Add onions and garlic to skillet for 1 to 2 minutes to absorb leftover roast juice. Place into roaster pan with meat and bay leaves.\
Combine the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mushroom/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mushroom}} soup, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/wine/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 wine}}, Worcestershire sauce and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/beef/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 beef}} bouillon into a bowl. Pour over the roast. Add water.\
Cover pan with foil and bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.\
Remove and discard the bay leaves.\
*Cook's Note: If the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/gravy/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 gravy}} is not thick enough, remove the meat from the pan and pour the gravy into a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}}. Bring to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/boil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 boil}} and thicken it by adding 2 tablespoons of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cornstarch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cornstarch}} mixed with 1/4 cup cold water, stirring constantly.\
